verbose_text: However, we also observed a consistent reduction in myc-MCTS1 immunoblotting signal in co-transfection assays with myc-MCTS1 and FLAG-DENR C37Y (see XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY C), suggesting in this context that the presence of DENR C37Y could influence myc-MCTS1 expression and, thus, lead to DENR-MCTS1 dysfunction.
